      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JALAPENO POPPER (4) flew the lids from the middle with a slick turn of foot before finishing second (29.94) and beaten 3 lengths over 510m at this track. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Overdue and is among the main hopes. SCOTCH ROCKET (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fifth (24.20) in a Grade 5 at this track. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Worth another chance. DIAMANTINA PEARL (8) is rarely out of the finish, recording 21 places from 40 starts. Finished second (23.96) at this track latest and might be close to finding winning form again. Has a good record here at this journey. Will give a great sight again. RUPEE RANGER (3) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to turn the form around.",
